{"word":"ὁμώνυμος","slug":"ὁμώνυμος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ὁμώνυμος</b></el> <el>(ὁμ-ώνῠμος, ον,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ὄνομα'><el>ὄνομα</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>having the same name</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; <el>τινι</el> <i>with</i> one, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; <el>τὸν ὁμ. ἐμαυτῷ</el> my own <i>namesake</i>, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b>:—as <a href='S:Substantive'>Subst.</a>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <el>ὁ σαυτοῦ</el> or <el>ὁ σὸς ὁμώνυμος</el> your <i>namesake</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>of like kind</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}